==English==
===Etymology===
From the Latin ''pubertas'', (adulthood), equivalent to ''puber'', (downy, adult) + ''-tas'', (Latin ending denoting state [of]).

===Noun===
'''puberty'''
{{wikipedia}}
# the age at which a person is first capable of sexual reproduction

